See http://www.pervalidus.net//lynx/ for additional information.

1- Make any changes to lynx.cfg, not lynx.cfg.dist. lynx.cfg includes
it.

2- I assume Lynx is installed in D:\Program Files\Lynx. If you use
another PATH, edit lynx.cfg and change

INCLUDE:D:\Program Files\Lynx\lynx.cfg.list

and

HELPFILE:file://localhost/D:/Program Files/Lynx/lynx_help/lynx_help_main.html.gz

accordingly.

3- If you want to use any other .lss files from the lynx_doc/samples/
directory, start lynx.exe with the -lss option.

Examples (if you're in D:\Program Files\Lynx):

lynx.exe -lss=lynx_doc/samples/blue-background.lss
lynx.exe -lss=lynx_doc/samples/bright-blue.lss
lynx.exe -lss=lynx_doc/samples/mild-colors.lss
